Company Overview of Contran Corporation, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Contran Corporation, Inc., through its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells titanium dioxide pigments in North America and Europe. It also offers manufacturing engineering components in the areas of security products, furniture components, and marine; and operating a treatment, storage, and disposal facility in Andrews, Texas. The company offers engineered components ranging from locks utilized in ignition systems, office furniture, and postal boxes; to precision slides used in filing cabinets, bottom mount freezers, and tool boxes; to ergonomic keyboard arms and flat panel monitor mounts, as well as gauges and exhaust systems for high-performance boats. In addition, it supplies titanium met...
Contran Corporation, Inc., through its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells titanium dioxide pigments in North America and Europe. It also offers manufacturing engineering components in the areas of security products, furniture components, and marine; and operating a treatment, storage, and disposal facility in Andrews, Texas. The company offers engineered components ranging from locks utilized in ignition systems, office furniture, and postal boxes; to precision slides used in filing cabinets, bottom mount freezers, and tool boxes; to ergonomic keyboard arms and flat panel monitor mounts, as well as gauges and exhaust systems for high-performance boats. In addition, it supplies titanium metal products to aerospace and industrial applications. The company offers solutions for the management of radioactive, hazardous, and mixed materials to government organizations, department of energy, department of defense, environmental protection agency, army corps of engineers, and commercial entities in the United States. It has titanium dioxide pigment manufacturing sites in North America and Europe. Contran Corporation, Inc. was incorporated in 1944 and is based in Dallas, Texas.
Detailed Description


